<br>
1)  As Whiz already mentioned, SK's can do damage that is greater then MB damage..has a faster casting time, faster refresh timer...doesn't leave the SK defensless/offensiveless (far from it) once used.  <br>
<br>
2)  Lifeburn... not nerfed to 75% damage.  Necro lifetaps, casts invulnerability (1.0 sec), then heals back to full using spells/potions (ala, no real penalty for using this skill).. <br>
<br>
3) Heals, are not,  have never been nerfed in PvP.  <br>
<br>
4) Offensive spells have now been nerfed 4-5 times on PvP servers .. 1st: 66% damage cap, 2nd: Line of sight ..(remember, they didn't want people casting MB through bank walls, (and rightfully so ) ?  Kind of a mute point now, yet restriction still lingers) 3rd: Refresh timers fixed (Staff of Temp Flux)  I know, this wasn't a nerf, but was a &quot;fix&quot; ..still, beyond a doubt, lessened our ability to cast faster, which is important to note.   4th: The latest, the 75% DD cap.<br>
<br>
I am not bitching, I am just stating the facts.  I like the resistant changes, makes things more realistic.  The 150% increase in PvP Debuffing spells about 2 years ago was a little limiting for Wizards (meaning, we became more dependant on our lure line for the majority of our encounters.)  If you have 150 + aa's, you can still hold your own as a wizard in PvP; however,  you can hold your own as well or better if you were another class with 50 + aa's.  This is the descrepency that bothers me on the PvP servers atm. I guess we also have our 'escapability', which can be an advantage ..maybe this is how Verant see's balance.  /shrug<br>
<br>
