<br>
If the ability were still amplified by ID focus items and could still land as a Critical Strike (caused by AA Fury line abilities) it would help make it more useful, even if a maximum cap on the damage was in place.<br>
<br>
The ability simply has too high a cost for too little an effect to be worth while, especially since we can get far more bang for our buck with spells, and spend the AA points on abilities and gear up with focus items that amplify said spells.<br>
<br>
They should have considered making an entirely new ability as opposed to making this one so worthless.  Perhaps an ability that let us &quot;burn Mana&quot; by providing a buff which lasted 20 seconds and any spells we cast in that time generate only 1 point of aggro a piece.  THAT would have been an ability worth spending 12 point on MC 1, 2, and 3, and 5 in class abilities for!<br>
<br>
