<br>
The Whole Game Is Not Dragon Fights.<br>
<br>
Oddly, I spend 99.9% of my time in EQ killing nameless, faceless hordes of mobs that have no point in being where they are or in chasing me while I nuke them, yet that's the way it is. Manaburn was fine for eradicating one of these, and I suppose, it still is for the most part anywhere against mobs &gt;53'ish.<br>
<br>
The fact that it leaves the wizard defenceless unless he has instant evac or the mob has no friends balanced it-- combined with it's insane recast time.<br>
<br>
Current non-crittable, no more than 1 per minute Manaburn would be balanced with a Recast of 15 min, and no mana drain, or with a Mana Recourse effect.  Big fights would only see 1 or 2 manaburns unless its stupid high HP mobs from vellious, Wizards could horribly damage a chosen victim often enough to be worthwhile--assuming they keep up their mana pool.  Oddly, this is harder than it sounds.  Not all wizards have FT gear, or Harvest2.<br>
