<br>
Maybe Manaburn should scale with your level?  A 10% increase in damage every level post 60?  That would work, that would make for a 50% increase at level 65, for average manaburns in the 10-15k range instead of the normal 6-9k range.  Of course, remove the cap, or move it to 15k, put crits back in, so someone at level 60 could crit for 15k.  That would not be unbalanced.<br>
<br>
Or add an improved manaburn which 50% more damage than the current manaburn, and possibly refreshes more often.  Make it available at level 65.<br>
<br>
Or take out the mana requirement, or at least make your mana regen to full again in say 30 seconds, so that it still fits in with the mana &quot;burn&quot; concept.<br>
<br>
Or just flat out make manaburn more efficient, take the cap off it, and allow for crits, but make that one-minute recast timer five minutes.  That would make it useful in xp groups, but marginally useful in raids.  Most of the encounters they are concerned about are fast encounters that are over in 5 mins...  one 15-20k nuke in 5 mins would not be imbalancing.<br>
<br>
There are lots of great ideas for changes which could be made to manaburn which would not make it unbalancing.  Tons.  The thing is that no one at Sony is listening to us and looking into our concerns, they are too busy fixing the protectors in PoG. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nandark>Nandark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/28/03 9:54:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26274.topic&index=57>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another manaburn post</span><hr size=1>  Actually, I don't mind the MB nerf due to the unbalancing aspect as in farming, however think a fair thing to do would be:<br>
