<br>
There are several reason why MB would be preferable to SoS in some encounters.<br>
<br>
First of all, SoS doesn't land on all mobs. There are some mobs that need to die ASAP due to the unreal amount of damage they do. With the insane amount of regen available on a raid, you can MB at 99%, click a mod rod, cast harvest x2 and still chain nuke until mod rod pops up again. If you are sitting on a horse you can even click a mana robe between casts, it's cast time is only .75 sec longer than refresh so it doesn't really affect DPS. In the case of a mob that is highly MR you can robe up 2-3 click between casts in the time you would have spend casting concussion.<br>
<br>
Second of all, manaburn is unresistable and for a high end wizard its practically a guaranteed 9kish damage. Due to the &quot;low&quot; damage cap, it doesn't take anywhere near being FM to be able to cap a burn. This means you can nuke for some time, burn for max, then click a rod and harvest and continue nuking.<br>
<br>
There are tons of mobs in PoP that have to die fast due to insane DPS, the AE effects, or to buy some time in time limited events, in any of those encounters being able to toss out 9k damage very quickly with no agro is a godsend. I think the point you are missing is that it's not a &quot;team of MB wizards&quot; burning down one mob, but rather an MB rotation where 1 wizard burns each mob as they are engaged.<br>
<br>
In the time it takes to cast 3x SoS to get the damage of a single MB (discounting a crit of course) you can get back enough mana to resume casting at a pretty reasonable pace so a well time MB will increase your DPS over time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nadiar>Nadiar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.nadiar.com/avatar.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Mistyr Smartipants</span><br>  Posts: 1065<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/29/03 2:58:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26274.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.nadiar.com/avatar.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another manaburn post</span><hr size=1> Stop comparing Manaburn to SoS.<br>
